{{Infobox country at games | NOC = PHI | NOCname = [[Philippine Olympic Committee]] | oldcode = | year = 1958 | date = | games = Asian Games | location = [[Tokyo]] | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | officials = | gold = 9 | silver = 19 | bronze = 21 | rank = 2 | appearances = auto | seealso = | website = {{URL|www.olympic.ph}}&nbsp;{{en icon}} }}
The '''[[Philippines]]''' participated in the [[1958 Asian Games]] held in [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]] from May 24 to June 1, 1958. The country ranked 2nd with 8 gold medals, 19 silver medals and 21 bronze medals.<ref>[http://www.ocasia.org/3AG.asp 1958 Asian Games medal tally] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070210073820/http://www.ocasia.org/3AG.asp |date=2007-02-10 }}</ref> This edition of the [[Asian Games|Asiad]] has been the most fruitful for the Philippines in terms of the total number of medals garnered.
==Asian Games performance== 148 athletes participated and they joined in 12 sports. Inocencia Solis was crowned Asia's fastest woman with a 12.5 second clocking, she also won the silver medal as part of the 4x100 near relay squad of Rogelia Ferrer, Francisca Sanopal and Irene Penuela.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}
The basketball squad won its third consecutive Asian Cage title.
