{{infobox country at games | NOC = TUR | NOCname = [[Turkish Olympic Committee|Turkish National Olympic Committee]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1908 | flagcaption = Flag of the [[Ottoman Empire]] | oldcode = | website = {{url|olimpiyat.org.tr }}&nbsp;{{en icon}} {{tr}} | location = [[London]] | competitors = 1 | sports = 1 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = [[Turkey at the 1906 Intercalated Games|1906]] Intercalated Games }}
The [[Ottoman Empire]] may have been represented by one athlete, [[Aleko Mulos]], at the '''[[1908 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[London]], [[United Kingdom|Britain]], but the official report is not clear as to whether he participated.<ref name=London>{{cite book|first=The fourth Olympiad: the official report of the Olympic games of London, 1908|title=The fourth Olympiad: the official report of the Olympic games of 1908, celebrated in London|publisher=The British Olympic Association|url=http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1908/1908.pdf|editor=Theodore Andrea Cook|accessdate=10 February 2013}}</ref> During the Olympics, the Ottoman Empire was referred to as [[Turkey]]. It was the first recognized appearance of the Ottoman State, though other athletes from Ottoman territories had previously competed for [[Kingdom of Greece|Greece]].{{fact|date=March 2014}}
